<p>
<p>Join us in downtown White River Junction for a fine First Friday on August 7th with a fantastic lineup of live music, cheap wine and fine art!</p><br /><p>Many thanks to Dave Clark &amp; Yellow House Media for arranging live music to play at locations all over downtown WRJ.</p><br /><p>This month, you can catch a little open mic at the Upper Valley Food Coop, an appearance by loop artist Vinnie Ramirez at Revolution,  James McGaw, Betsy Stewart, EJ Tretter, and Wood n' Henne in the Tip Top Building from 6pm to 8pm and two bands (The Outsiders &amp; Signs of Sanity) trading 30 minutes sets in the Gates Briggs Parking Lot! </p><br /><p>Dave Clark plays at Big Fatty's from 6pm to 8pm and then hosts an open mic for First Friday musicians.</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Two-Rivers-Printmaking-Studio/272733412519?fref=ts" target="_blank">The Two Rivers Printmaking Studio</a> features an opening reception with prints by a dozen artists who took workshops at Two Rivers over the past few months including collagraphs, monoprints, viscosity prints, woodblock printing, and concertina books.  85 North Main Street.  5-8pm. </p><br /><p>      <br /><a href="https://www.facebook.com/ScavengerGallery?fref=ts" target="_blank">Scavenger Gallery</a> presents an exhibition of 'Recombination Art' from 'Kulture Mavens', Powell + Peberdy, plus Stacy's phenomenal collection of hand crafted jewelry &amp; a wine tasting from Artisanal Cellars. 41 South Main Street. 5:30-7:30pm </p><br /><p>The Half and Half Troupe perform A Dramedy Variety Show on the stage at the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/HotelCoolidge?fref=ts" target="_blank">Briggs Opera House</a> (former location of Northern Stage Theater).  Past and present students from the Hanover High School Footlighters along with students from the <br />highly acclaimed theater program at Muhlenberg College present an evening of sketch comedy, improv, short plays, music and dance. Donations accepted at the door.  Briggs Opera House, 5 South Main Street. 7:30pm</p><br /><p>The innovative team at <a href="http://www.opendoorworkshop.com/" target="_blank">Open Door</a> are hosting a FUN-Raiser supporting World Story Exchange including a photo booth, music and face painting. 18 North Main Street.  5-8pm.</p><br /><p>Our friends at the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/mainstreetmuseum?fref=ts" target="_blank">Main Street Museum </a>invite you to 'A Marvelous Dinner'.  Candlelight, torches, music,<br /> entertainment &amp; wonders + Tarot &amp; Crystal Ball consultation included!  $60 per person.  RSVP to info [at] mainstreetmuseum [dot] org. 58 Bridge Street. 6pm. </p><br /><p>Stop by <a href="http://northernstage.org/" target="_blank">Northern Stage's </a>new location for Hard Hat Happy Hour from 5-6pm with tours of the new building departing at 5pm &amp; 6pm!  Call the box office for details.  <br /> 802.296.7000</p><br /><p>The <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Upper-Valley-Food-Coop/106601659402589?fref=ts" target="_blank">Upper Valley Food Coop </a>offers all shoppers a 5% discount and delicious food samples &amp; all things rhubarb accompanied by the "Grand Ol' Co-opry" live music series.193 North Main Street. 4-6:30pm.</p><br /><p>First Friday is Ladies Night at the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/raqondance?fref=ts" target="_blank">Raq-On Dance Studio</a>!  This month Amity is featuring Dancing with Feather Fans with Abi. No prior experience necessary. $10 per person. Register online at raq-on [dot] net.  241 South Main Street.  7pm. </p><br /><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/uppervalleyyoga?fref=ts" target="_blank">Upper Valley Yoga</a> offers their uplifting Yin Yoga on First Friday. Free!  58 North Main Street. 5:30-6:45pm.</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Big-Fattys-BBQ-Hartford/232528713435764?fref=ts" target="_blank">Big Fatty's BBQ</a> has a new location on South Main Street (near Elixir) where they'll be serving the best BBQ in the UV and hosting live music in to the evening on First Friday. 186 South Main Street. 11am- 9pm. </p><br /><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/tuckerbox.vermont?fref=ts" target="_blank">The Tuckerbox</a> is now serving delicious Mediterranean cuisine. Be sure to make dinner reservations at the Tbox or <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Elixir-Restaurant/191339870885504?fref=ts" target="_blank">Elixir </a>or <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Tip-Top-Cafe/128654930557139?fref=ts" target="_blank">Tip Top Cafe</a>.</p>
